description: A Rohrflöte of 2-2/3' pitch. The name Rohrquinte has also been used as a synonym for Rohrflötenquinte. The name Nasard en Cheminée appears only in a sample stoplist in Dom Bedos. Nasards of that period commonly were made with chimneyed basses and conical trebles (see Nasard à Fuseau).
examplesDescription: No examples of Nasard en Cheminée are known. Contributions welcome.
